SIMPLE: incautious
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Incautious
<hw>In*cau"tious</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>in-</ets> not + <ets>cautious</ets>: cf. L.
<ets>incautus</ets>.]</ety> <def>Not cautious; not circumspect; not
attending to the circumstances on which safety and interest depend;
heedless; careless; <as>as, an <ex>incautious</ex> step; an
<ex>incautious</ex> remark.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 743 --></p>

<p><q>You . . . <qex>incautious</qex> tread⟦br⟧
On fire with faithless embers overspread.</q>
<rj><qau>Francis.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His rhetorical expressions may easily captivate any
<qex>incautious</qex> reader.</q> <rj><qau>Keill.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Unwary; indiscreet; inconsiderate; imprudent;
impolitic; careless; heedless; thoughtless.</syn></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>In*cau"tious*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>In*cau"tious*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Incavated</ent>⟦br⟧
